Anh - Anh
Norwegian
[nɔ:'wi:dʒ(ə)n]
■ noun
1》 a native or national of Norway, or a person of Norwegian descent.
2》 the Scandinavian language spoken in Norway.
■ adjective relating to Norway or its people or language.
Origin
from med. L. Norvegia 'Norway' (from ON Norvegr, lit. 'north way') + -an.
